This is the Atrinik Map Maker package. Below you'll find instructions how to
use this package.

#####################
#      Windows      #
#####################

== Map Editor ==

To run Gridarta for Atrinik - the Atrinik map editor - you'll need Java 1.6 or later.
Download it from the Java website (http://www.java.com).

Note that on some versions of Java (generally the newer ones), you have to manually
set the PATH environment variable. See http://www.jibble.org/settingupjava.php for
instructions.

When you're finished setting up Java, double-click w32_start_editor.bat to start the
editor.

== Server ==

You need to download Python 3.3 from the Python website (http://www.python.org) and install
it to the default location.

Simply double-click w32_start_server.bat and the server should start.

== Client ==

Double-click w32_start_client.bat.

== Map Checker ==

Map checker is a tool to check your maps located in tools/map-checker. To run it, you need
Python 2.7 and PyGTK, which can be downloaded here: http://www.pygtk.org

Then simply execute map-checker.py in tools/map-checker with Python.

#####################
#     GNU/Linux     #
#####################

== Map Editor ==

Download Java 1.6 or later from the Java website (http://www.java.com) or install it using
your favorite package manager. Then use:

sh linux_start_client.sh

== Server ==

Use your favorite package manager to install Python 3.3 (or compile it from source).
Then use this command:

sh linux_start_server.sh

== Client ==

Use this command to start up the client:

sh linux_start_client.sh

== Map Checker ==

Map checker is a tool to check your maps located in tools/map-checker. To run it, you need
Python 2.7 (which you should have by now from the above server step) and PyGTK, which you
can install using your favorite package manager. After that, run this command:

python2.7 tools/map-checker/map-checker.py
